# Staylight — Scope Control

**Hard constraints.** Do not add these unless the user explicitly requests them in a future session:

| Out of scope | Reason |
|---|---|
| Authentication / user accounts | Mock app; no login |
| Real payments (Stripe, etc.) | Mocked checkout only |
| Maps (Google Maps, Mapbox) | Not required |
| Admin dashboard | Out of scope |
| Host dashboard | Out of scope |
| Saved favorites / wishlists | Out of scope |
| Messaging / chat | Out of scope |
| AI chat / LLM integration | Smart Match is rule-based only |
| External travel APIs | Seeded data only |
| Real database (Postgres, Supabase, etc.) | Seed data in `lib/data` |

## When in Doubt

- Keep data **seeded and simple** (in-memory or file-based mutations during a session are OK; persist to seed module if needed for demo continuity)
- **Prioritize the full booking flow** over new features
- A feature not listed in project-objective is likely out of scope — ask before building

## Allowed Mock Behaviors

- Simulated payment form with fake card fields and a "Complete booking (demo)" CTA
- Booking confirmation with generated reference number
- Adding a review appends to in-memory/seed data for the session
